  "prompt": "What is usoclient.exe on Windows 10?",
  "response": "Usoclient.exe is a legitimate Windows 10 system process related to the Windows Update service. Specifically:\n\n1. Purpose:\n- Manages Windows Update downloads and installations\n- Helps coordinate system updates and Windows Update features\n- Part of the Update Orchestrator service\n\n2. Location:\n- Typically found in: C:\\Windows\\System32 folder\n\n3. Functionality:\n- Handles update scanning, downloading, and installation\n- Helps manage update notifications\n- Assists in background update processes\n\n4. Normal behavior:\n- Runs periodically to check for and install system updates\n- Generally consumes minimal system resources\n- Should not cause significant CPU or memory usage\n\n5. Safety:\n- Is a genuine Microsoft Windows component\n- Not a virus or malware\n- Part of normal Windows operating system functionality\n\nIf you notice unusually high resource consumption by usoclient.exe, it might indicate an ongoing update process or potential system update issues.",
